TITLE: HTML data-e2e Attribute Example
DESCRIPTION: This HTML snippet demonstrates the usage of the `data-e2e` attribute for uniquely identifying elements for E2E testing. This helps target specific elements in tests, even if they have similar classes or tags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/module-federation/module-federation-examples/blob/master/cypress-e2e/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<div class="form-group">
  <input
    type="text"
    class="form-control"
    formControlName="name"
    placeholder="Name"
    #name
    data-e2e="FORM_FIELD__NAME"
  />
  <div
    *ngIf="angForm.controls['name'].invalid && (angForm.controls['name'].dirty || angForm.controls['name'].touched)"
    class="alert alert-danger"
  >
    <div *ngIf="angForm.controls['name'].errors.required">Name is required.</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

